Classification.Comment: The detected CNV was reported as a 3q27.1 microdeletion in 10 cases from literature, with the main phenotypes being intrauterine growth restriction, short stature, neurodevelopmental abnormalities, distinctive facial dysmorphisms, and cardiac defects. These clinical features are present in our patient. However, a clear association with urogenital anomalies has not yet been reported. Micropenis, cryptorchidism, and other minor urogenital anomalies have been described, but without comprehensive study or diagnosis (PMID: 35241116; PMID: 23357683). Classification score: 1.45 following the ACMG/ClinGen CNV Guidelines, 2021 (PMID: 33731880).
